SIMPLE: octopus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Octopus
<hw>Oc"to*pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Octopod</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
eight-armed cephalopods, including numerous species, some of them of
large size. See <er>Devilfish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any member of the genus
<gen>Octopus</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <mark>(Fig.)</mark> <def>Something resembling an octopus
in having numerous controlling arms or branches that reach widely and
influence many activities; -- used mostly of organizations, such as
diversified corporations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Octoradiated</ent>⟦br⟧
